issue.title: Update bindgen requirement from 0.64 to 0.65

labels.name: dependencies
labels.description: Pull requests that update a dependency file

labels.name: rust
labels.description: Pull requests that update Rust code

issue.body:
Updates the requirements on [bindgen](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust-bindgen) to permit the latest version.
Changelog

Sourced from bindgen's changelog.

0.65.0

Added

  • Added the Builder::default_visibility method and the --default-visibility flag to set the default visibility of fields. (#2338)
  • Added the --formatter CLI flag with the values none, rustfmt and prettyplease to select which tool will be used to format the bindings. The default value is rustfmt. (#2453)
  • Added the Builder::formatter method and the Formatter type to select which tool will be used to format the bindings. (#2453)
  • Added the Builder::emit_diagnostics method and the --emit-diagnostics flag to enable emission of diagnostic messages under the experimental feature. (#2436)
  • Added support for the "efiapi" calling convention (#2490).
  • Added the ParseCallbacks::read_env_var method which runs everytime bindgen reads and environment variable. (#2400)
  • Added the ParseCallbacks::generated_link_name_override method which allow overriding the link name of items. (#2425)
  • Add support for C enums when generating code while using the --wrap-static-fns feature. (#2415)

Changed

  • Static functions with no arguments use void as their single argument instead of having no arguments when the --wrap-static-fns flag is used. (#2443)
  • The source file generated when the --wrap-static-fns flag is enabled now contains #include directives with all the input headers and all the source code added with the header_contents method. (#2447)
  • The source file generated when the --wrap-static-fns flag no longer uses asm labeling and the link name of static wrapper functions is allowed to be mangled. (#2448)
  • The documentation of the generated type aliases now matches the comments of their typedef counterparts instead of using the comments of the aliased types. (#2463)
  • The Builder::rustfmt_bindings methods and the --no-rustfmt-bindings flag are now deprecated in favor of the formatter API. (#2453)

Removed

  • The following deprecated flags were removed: --use-msvc-mangling, --rustfmt-bindings and --size_t-is-usize. (#2408)
  • The Bindings::emit_warnings and Bindings::warnings methods were removed in favor of --emit-diagnostics. (#2436)
  • Bindgen no longer generates C string constants that cannot be represented as byte slices. (#2487)

0.64.0

Added

  • Added a new set of flags --with-derive-custom, --with-derive-custom-struct, --with-derive-custom-enum and

... (truncated)

Commits
  • 2bcff0f Prepare to release 0.65.0 (#2492)
  • 54bf9ca Make prettyplease non-optional (#2491)
  • 5d1c79a bindgen::ParseCallbacks: support tracking env variable usage for cargo (#2400)
  • 1e3e25f Document efiapi ABI stabilization (#2490)
  • 594eb7b Add support for the "efiapi" ABI. (#2481)
  • dcc21c1 Don't generate wrong strings. (#2487)
  • f03d4f4 Typo: Update CHANGELOG.md (#2489)
  • 281180c Add minimal workflow (#2483)
  • be2f59c Fix unused_code warnings without experimental (#2482)
  • 0f1a404 Apply the C-EVOCATIVE guideline to options! (#2480)
  • Additional commits viewable in compare view

issue.title: patching SPHINCS again
issue.body:
This may be a better approach to correcting the AVX2 integration problem wrt common code: This adds a patch again removing the project-specific `fips202x4.h/c` files.

HOWEVER, changes were necessary to the common code declarations to permit this to compile: See src/common/pqclean_shims/fips202x4.h below.

This clearly is not quite right given that the tests don't pass -- but that makes me wonder: Is the common code implementation of `KeccakP1600times4_PermuteAll_24rounds` possibly not quite what the new Sphincs+ code base expects/has built-in? If @jschanck would have time to glance this over, this would be great, given that his PR https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/liboqs/pull/948 did things correctly the last time.

comment.body:
@bwesterb changed how SPHINCS+ works by directly integrating the Keccak permutation in a few more places than just `fips202x4`. This means that the way that liboqs has offered its shims to SPHINCS+ is no longer compatible. 

I had a lot of trouble getting this to work in my quick-and-dirty integration of SPHINCS+ [here](https://github.com/thomwiggers/liboqs/tree/dirty-oqs-thesis-benchmarks). This only compiles with very specific flags to CMake, as the namespacing of `KeccakP1600` also seems to change depending on them.

issue.title: Upgrade to OpenSSL3
issue.body: As per https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/openssl/discussions/434#discussioncomment-5421852 switching another downstream project. Performance impacts of this will be interesting to observe (see also https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/liboqs/pull/1431 necessitating further updates to downstream projects)

comment.body: Looks fine to me, but I'll let Douglas have the last word.
